{
  "text": " Hi mom it's me. Sometimes it's hard for me to say it face to face about how I've left you all along. Now that Mother's Day is near it's easier for me to say how I feel in this song. Those tender tears my mother shed for me. For my hurt feelings she offered sympathy. Through both the good times and the bad she was the one true friend I always had. When I was scared she'd say it'll be alright. When I was sick she stayed up through the night. She kissed my sores and my tears away. Made time for me during her busy day. She sheltered me from all harm through the years. She kept me safe and warm. When I was growing up she was always there. When I was bad she was firm but fair. She did her best to teach me right from wrong. And now my heart carries her loving song. Thanks for loving what you gave to me. Thanks for not giving up when I was mean as I could be. Mom I love you more than words can say. And this is your song on Mother's Day.",
